FLAG --indicator-style=WORD : Specify what indicators to use.

    This flag lets you control which indicator characters
    are used to describe entries in the results. Almost all
    of them have equivalent short versions, which you can
    look up for more information about indicators.

--indicator-style=none

    Default. No indicators. Useful for overriding other
    flags.

--indicator-style=slash

    Append / to the end of directory entries.

    Equivalent to -p.

--indicator-style=file-type

    Use all indicators except '*' (otherwise used to label
    files as executable).

    Equivalent to --file-type.

--indicator-style=classify

    Use all indicator types, don't hold back.

    Equivalent to -F.

